Emerging-market equities and currencies posted their biggest weekly gains since June as the prospect of renewed U.S.-China trade talks, expectations of a September Fed rate cut and easing tensions in Hong Kong bolstered risk sentiment. Central banks in Chile, China and Russia eased monetary policies by cutting interest rates or the required reserve ratio. The following is a roundup of emerging-markets news and highlights for the week ending Sept. 6. Highlights: EMEA: